AGENT AxiomMCPServer
VERSION 0.1
TRUST_LEVEL 3
PURPOSE Expose AXIOM constitutional governance tools via MCP JSON-RPC 2.0 over stdio
GOAL Serve 5 constitutional tools (guard_check, lint, trace, qrf, status) as an MCP server,
     reading JSON-RPC requests from stdin and writing responses to stdout, with HMAC-signed
     results and proper error handling for unknown tools and malformed input

RECEIVES JSON-RPC 2.0 requests over stdin
EMITS JSON-RPC 2.0 responses over stdout
MUTATES nothing
CANNOT_MUTATE version, trust_level

CONSTRAINT VERSION is 1.8.7 and CANNOT_MUTATE
CONSTRAINT TRUST_LEVEL is 3 and CANNOT_MUTATE
CONSTRAINT Every tool result includes hmac_signature field
CONSTRAINT Every response is valid JSON-RPC 2.0 with jsonrpc id and result or error
CONSTRAINT Unknown tool name in tools/call emits error response not crash
CONSTRAINT Invalid JSON input emits JSON-RPC parse error code -32700
CONSTRAINT All payloads are UTF-8 encoded before HMAC signing per BUG-003 and BUG-008
CONSTRAINT HMAC signing always calls hexdigest explicitly per BUG-007

RULES
- On initialize: emit protocolVersion capabilities and serverInfo
- On tools/list: emit all 5 tool definitions with name description and inputSchema
- On tools/call: route to correct handler by tool name
- On tools/call: wrap result in content array with type text and JSON text
- On tools/call with unknown tool: emit JSON-RPC error code -32000
- On invalid JSON: emit JSON-RPC parse error code -32700
- On unknown method: emit JSON-RPC method not found error code -32601
- On axiom_guard_check: run validate_output and LatentTrace encode_heuristic
- On axiom_lint: write spec to temp file run lint_file and clean up
- On axiom_trace: run LatentEngine heuristic trajectory and extract 3 stages
- On axiom_qrf: run QRFEngine forecast with domain mapping
- On axiom_status: check guard API and test count

PROCESS
- Server receives JSON-RPC lines from stdin and emits responses to stdout
- Each request is parsed and routed by method field
- On initialize: protocol version and capabilities are established
- On tools/list: all 5 tool definitions with inputSchema are emitted
- On tools/call: handler is selected by name and result wrapped in MCP content format
- On error: JSON-RPC error response is emitted with code and message
- Server processes requests until stdin reaches EOF

CHECK
- VERSION assignment raises AttributeError
- tools/call with unknown tool emits error not crash
- Invalid JSON emits parse error code -32700
- tools/list emits all 5 tools with schemas
- axiom_guard_check emits verdict and hmac_signature
- axiom_lint emits health_score
- Every response is valid JSON-RPC 2.0
- Every tool result includes hmac_signature
- Error responses include error code and message

FAILURE
- On invalid JSON: emit parse error -32700 with null id
- On unknown method: emit method not found -32601
- On handler exception: emit internal error -32000 with message

CONCEPT MCPTransport
PURPOSE Read JSON-RPC requests from stdin and write responses to stdout
APPLIES WHEN server is running and receiving input
NOT WHEN stdin is closed or EOF reached
PRIORITY 1
REQUIRES stdin and stdout with UTF-8 encoding
EFFECT Line-delimited JSON-RPC communication

CONCEPT MCPToolRegistry
PURPOSE Maintain registry of 5 constitutional tools with inputSchema definitions
APPLIES WHEN tools/list is requested by client
NOT WHEN server is not yet initialized
PRIORITY 1
REQUIRES tool definitions with name description and inputSchema
EFFECT Complete tool list emitted to client

CONCEPT MCPHandler
PURPOSE Route tools/call requests to correct handler and wrap results
APPLIES WHEN tools/call is received with valid tool name
NOT WHEN tool name is unknown or arguments are invalid
PRIORITY 1
REQUIRES tool name and arguments dict from JSON-RPC params
EFFECT Tool result wrapped in MCP content format with HMAC signature

OUTPUT
- JSON-RPC 2.0 responses with result or error
- Tool results wrapped in content array format

SUCCESS
valid_jsonrpc_responses:         0.20
all_tools_registered:            0.15
hmac_signatures_present:         0.20
error_handling_correct:          0.20
cannot_mutate_enforced:          0.10
transport_reliable:              0.15
